---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Nav from '../../components/Nav.astro';
import Footer from '../../components/Footer.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Mud Weight Window Calculator — Visualize Your Safe Drilling Range"
  description="Calculate and visualize your mud weight window between pore pressure and fracture gradient at any depth, with margin analysis in both psi and ppg."
  breadcrumbs={[{ label: 'Calculators', href: '/calculators' }, { label: 'Mud Weight Window', href: '/calculators/mud-weight-window' }]}
  lang="en"
  alternateHref="/es/calculators/mud-weight-window"
>
  <Nav slot="nav" lang="en" alternateHref="/es/calculators/mud-weight-window" />
  <Footer slot="footer" lang="en" />

  <div class="page-hero">
    <div class="page-hero-eyebrow">Calculator</div>
    <h1>Mud Weight <span>Window Calculator</span></h1>
    <p class="page-hero-sub">Visualize how wide — or narrow — your safe drilling window is at a given depth, and see your current mud weight plotted against it.</p>
  </div>

  <section class="block">
    <div class="two-col">
      <div>
        <div class="calc-box">
          <div class="calc-title">📊 Mud Weight Window</div>

          <div class="input-row">
            <div class="input-group">
              <label for="mww-tvd">TVD (ft)</label>
              <input type="number" id="mww-tvd" placeholder="e.g. 10000" step="100" min="100">
            </div>
            <div class="input-group">
              <label for="mww-current">Current Mud Weight (ppg)</label>
              <input type="number" id="mww-current" placeholder="e.g. 12.0" step="0.1">
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="input-row">
            <div class="input-group">
              <label for="mww-pp">Pore Pressure Gradient (ppg equiv.)</label>
              <input type="number" id="mww-pp" placeholder="e.g. 9.2" step="0.1">
            </div>
            <div class="input-group">
              <label for="mww-fg">Fracture Gradient (ppg equiv.)</label>
              <input type="number" id="mww-fg" placeholder="e.g. 15.0" step="0.1">
            </div>
          </div>

          <button class="btn btn-primary" id="calc-mww-btn" style="width:100%;text-align:center;">Calculate Window</button>

          <div class="calc-output" id="mww-output">
            <div class="output-line"><span class="output-label">Window Width</span><span class="output-value" id="out-window">—</span></div>
            <div class="output-line"><span class="output-label">Margin Above Pore Pressure</span><span class="output-value" id="out-margin-low">—</span></div>
            <div class="output-line"><span class="output-label">Margin Below Fracture</span><span class="output-value" id="out-margin-high">—</span></div>
            <div class="output-line" style="border-bottom:none;"><span class="output-label">Position</span><span id="out-position">—</span></div>
          </div>

          <div id="mww-visual" style="display:none;margin-top:20px;">
            <div style="height:36px;border-radius:3px;overflow:hidden;position:relative;background:var(--iron);">
              <div id="mww-bar-fill" style="height:100%;background:linear-gradient(90deg, var(--danger), var(--safe), var(--danger));position:relative;"></div>
              <div id="mww-marker" style="position:absolute;top:-6px;width:3px;height:48px;background:var(--white);box-shadow:0 0 6px rgba(255,255,255,0.6);"></div>
            </div>
            <div style="display:flex;justify-content:space-between;margin-top:6px;">
              <span style="font-family:var(--mono);font-size:10px;color:var(--fog);">Pore Pressure</span>
              <span style="font-family:var(--mono);font-size:10px;color:var(--fog);">Fracture Pressure</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="prose">
        <h2>What Is the Mud Weight Window?</h2>
        <p>The mud weight window is the range of mud weights (expressed here in ppg-equivalent for simplicity) that keeps your wellbore safely between two limits: heavy enough to prevent formation fluid influx (a kick), and light enough to avoid fracturing the formation and losing circulation.</p>
        <p>In normally pressured, geologically simple formations, this window can be several ppg wide — comfortable room for error. In depleted reservoirs, overpressured shales, or deepwater wells, the window can narrow to less than 0.5 ppg, requiring extremely tight mud weight control and often managed pressure drilling (MPD) techniques.</p>

        <h3>How to Read the Visual</h3>
        <p>The bar represents your window from pore pressure (left, red) through the safe zone (center, green) to fracture pressure (right, red). The white marker shows exactly where your current mud weight sits. A marker near either edge means very little margin for error — a small pressure fluctuation could push you into kick or lost-circulation territory.</p>

        <h2>Where to Get Real Pore & Fracture Data</h2>
        <p>This calculator uses figures you supply — for actual well planning, pore pressure is predicted from offset well data, seismic velocity analysis, and while-drilling indicators (like the d-exponent method), while fracture gradient is measured directly via a Leak-Off Test (LOT) at each casing shoe. See the <a href="/drilling/casing">casing design page</a> for how these figures drive casing point selection.</p>

        <p>For raw pressure-vs-depth calculations, use the <a href="/calculators/hydrostatic">hydrostatic pressure calculator</a>. If you're already shut in on a kick, go straight to the <a href="/calculators/kill-sheet">kill sheet calculator</a>.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<script>
  const btn = document.getElementById('calc-mww-btn');
  btn?.addEventListener('click', () => {
    const current = parseFloat((document.getElementById('mww-current') as HTMLInputElement).value);
    const pp = parseFloat((document.getElementById('mww-pp') as HTMLInputElement).value);
    const fg = parseFloat((document.getElementById('mww-fg') as HTMLInputElement).value);

    if (!current || !pp || !fg) {
      alert('Please fill in mud weight, pore pressure, and fracture gradient fields.');
      return;
    }

    if (fg <= pp) {
      alert('Fracture gradient must be greater than pore pressure gradient.');
      return;
    }

    const window = fg - pp;
    const marginLow = current - pp;
    const marginHigh = fg - current;

    (document.getElementById('out-window') as HTMLElement).textContent = window.toFixed(2) + ' ppg';
    (document.getElementById('out-margin-low') as HTMLElement).textContent = marginLow.toFixed(2) + ' ppg';
    (document.getElementById('out-margin-high') as HTMLElement).textContent = marginHigh.toFixed(2) + ' ppg';

    const statusEl = document.getElementById('out-position') as HTMLElement;
    if (current < pp) {
      statusEl.innerHTML = '<span class="status-badge status-danger">🚨 Below Pore Pressure</span>';
    } else if (current > fg) {
      statusEl.innerHTML = '<span class="status-badge status-danger">⛔ Above Fracture Pressure</span>';
    } else if (marginLow < 0.3 || marginHigh < 0.3) {
      statusEl.innerHTML = '<span class="status-badge status-caution">⚠ Narrow Margin</span>';
    } else {
      statusEl.innerHTML = '<span class="status-badge status-safe">✅ Within Safe Window</span>';
    }

    // Visual marker position
    const pct = Math.max(0, Math.min(100, ((current - pp) / window) * 100));
    const marker = document.getElementById('mww-marker') as HTMLElement;
    marker.style.left = `calc(${pct}% - 1.5px)`;
    (document.getElementById('mww-visual') as HTMLElement).style.display = 'block';

    document.getElementById('mww-output')?.classList.add('visible');
  });
</script>
